            "text": "We address an important problem in sequence-to-sequence ( Seq2Seq ) learning ",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "referred to as copying , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "in which certain segments in the input sequence are selectively replicated in the output sequence . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "A similar phenomenon is observable in human language communication . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "For example , humans tend to repeat entity names or even long phrases in conversation . <S>",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The challenge with regard to copying in Seq2Seq is that new machinery is needed ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "to decide when to perform the operation . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "In this paper , we incorporate copying into neural networkbased Seq2Seq learning ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "and propose a new model ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "called COPYNET with encoderdecoder structure . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "COPYNET can nicely integrate the regular way of word generation in the decoder with the new copying mechanism ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "which can choose subsequences in the input sequence ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "and put them at proper places in the output sequence . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "Our empirical study on both synthetic data sets and real world data sets demonstrates the efficacy of COPYNET . <S>",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
